        "id": 257282,
        "name": "Adioe3",
        "username": "adioe3",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/adioe3/{size}/49960_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-15T05:59:08.643Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal is currently using 10+GB on my 64 gig iPhone. I would love to be able to download all media from all chats (ideally as an archive). I’ve tried downloading files one by one but it is a large number of small files (mostly images) and this uses iOS sharing feature which seems to break down if it’s more than 10-20 files or more than 10 MB.</p>\n<p>So it would take an ice age to transfer the last 4 years of media from conversations going one by one, especially considering after sharing the media view is closed and I have to reopen and navigate back to where I was.</p>\n<p>It would be awesome if we could:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>have an option to stream all the media down from the primary device to Signal Desktop as a zip/rar/xz archive</li>\n<li>have an option then to (easily) delete all media from all chats (f.ex. by selecting chats we want to wipe media from)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>That way I’d have a backup of all my files and images and wouldn’t have to go buy a phone with more storage (this is the only problem I have with the device).</p>\n<p>Please please pretty please can we implement something like this?</p>\n<p>Thanks muchly!</p>\n<p>P.S. I regularly donate and am a programmer (but not a Typescript or Swift coder), if there’s any way to speed this up let me know. I’d throw more cash at it but am just another wage slave like the lot of us :/</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2024-12-15T05:59:08.643Z",
