        "created_at": "2024-12-15T06:23:28.492Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal is working on cloud backups which should allow you to offset media to be encrypted in the cloud to save space on the device.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"335\" data-topic=\"2798\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/whatnoww/48/54328_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/encrypted-cloud-backups/2798/335\">Encrypted cloud backups</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    There are no absolutes. It’s going to totally depends on your model.\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
